INSERT INTO biobank VALUES (834, 'Association study of coronary heart disease (CHD) Risk factors in the Genome using an Old-versus-young Setting', 'ARGOS: The Ã¢ÂÄÂòAssociation study of coronary heart disease (CHD) Risk factors in the Genome using an Old-versus-young SettingÃ¢ÂÄÂô (ARGOS-NL) population consisted of 500 patients, who were selected from 17000 FH patients with an identified causal mutation in the LDLR gene (segregating in the families and not present in controls) from the nationwide molecular screening program for FH. They were recruited from 38 lipid and cardiology clinics in the Netherlands in the nationwide molecular screening program of the Ã¢ÂÄÂòStichting Opsporing Erfelijke Familiare Hypercholesterolemie (StOEH)Ã¢ÂÄÂô.9 Phenotypic data (including CHD events) were acquired from general practitioners and by reviewing medical records at the lipid and cardiologic clinics.; Hartstichting number NHS-2006B190', 'bbmri-eric:ID:NL_211');
